ological and philosophic ramifications of these inquiries, they offer a bold challenge to contemporary anthropology to undertake a more rigorous examination of its own practices, blind spots, and capacities, in order to meet the demands of our day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aInquiry (Theory of knowledge) 0aInquiry (Theory of knowledge). 0aResearchxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aResearch. 0aSocial sciencesxFieldworkxElectronic books. 0aSocial sciencesxFieldwork. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aStavrianakis, Anthony, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226037073423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226037073/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles